ns offrir à nos clients une expérience de service inégalée, et cela d’un océan à l’autre\".\r\n<h3><b>À propos D’IDS Solutions</b></h3>\r\nIDS Solutions offrait ses services de gestion des documents aux entreprises de l\'Est du Canada. IDS a été formé en 2011 par la fusion de cinq sociétés indépendantes spécialisées dans les services d\'impression. Basé en Ontario, le principal objectif de l’entreprise était de créer une plate-forme d’affaires unique qui inclut les appareils d’impression et autres produits connexes ainsi que des services d\'entretien et de conseil en technologies de l\'information.\r\n\r\nLes différentes divisions d’IDS Solutions comprenaient : Ontario Data Supplies (ODS), EBQM inc., Cell-ANet inc, National Print Services Alliance, IDS Ricoh, DCI Service, et CNC Office Systems Limited.\r\n\r\nSource:\r\n\r\nMarc Lamarre\r\n\r\nDirecteur du développement organisationnel et des communications\r\n\r\nGroupe CT\r\n\r\n1 800-967-3103 / mlamarre@ctgroupect.com','CT Copieur fait l’acquisition de IDS Solutions','','inherit','closed','closed','','727-revision-v1','','','2017-06-29 20:01:10','2017-06-29 20:01:10','',727,'https://groupect.staging.ctrlweb.ca/2017/06/29/727-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(729,2,'2017-06-29 20:02:59','2017-06-29 20:02:59','<strong>Laval (Québec), April 7, 2016 -</strong> CT Copieur officially announces that it is acquiring the assets of IDS Solutions. The transaction will accelerate the implementation of CT Copieur’s growth strategy by significantly reinforcing its presence in the Canadian market.\r\n\r\n\"This acquisition will expand our business scope in Montreal, Québec and Toronto, it will consolidate ourpresence in Quebec and it will help us pursue our market strategy, which is to expand our business nationally\" says Tomy Bélanger, President of CT Copieur.\r\n<h3>The transition</h3>\r\nThe transition has been orchestrated by CT Copieur’s management team for several weeks now. The objective is to ensure optimal and full service to IDS Solutions’ customers regarding technical and administrative support, including sales. In this transition, the majority of IDS Solutions’ employees migrated within CT Copieur’s workforce.\r\n<h3>About CT Copieur</h3>\r\nCT Copieur provides complete and innovative consulting services with regards to sales, rental and maintenance to improve companies’ document flow management throughout advanced technologies. Founded in 1987, CT Copieur has been continually growing and raising its quality standards with regards to customer service. The company offers proactive, flexible and quick solutions to ensure optimum performance and increased productivity for businesses\' document workflows. Among the largest players of the Canadian marketplace, CT Copieur offers Canada-wide services and equipment for all business’ printing and document workflow management needs. With over 100 employees in its Québec City, Montreal and Toronto facilities, the company has the expertise to continue its growth strategy by deploying its acquisition activities nationwide.\r\n\r\nTomy Bélanger, President of CT Copieur quotes: \"Our company’s main objective is to offer our customers the best consulting service in the industry. By strengthening our position in the marketplace, we want to offer our customers an unforgettable service, coast to coast\".\r\n<h3>About IDS Solutions</h3>\r\nBased in Ontario, Canada, IDS was the leading independent managed print services provider in Eastern Canada. IDS was formed in 2011 through the combination of five of the region\'s leading independent managed print services companies, creating a unique, broad platform, that includes printing equipment and other products as well as equipment maintenance services and related IT consulting.\r\n\r\nCompanies that operated under the IDS Group: IDS Solutions, CNC Office Systems, Cell-A-Net, EBQM,\r\n\r\nNational Print Service Alliance, Ontario Data Supplies.\r\n\r\nSource:\r\n\r\nMarc Lamarre\r\n\r\nDirecteur du dév